    "body": "> > ` constructor(address initialOwner) Ownable(initialOwner){ }`\r\n> \r\n> We don't do that kind of constructor inheritance, because it messes up multiple inheritance very fast.\r\n\r\nI second that we usually avoid it, but we might consider it in some cases. For example, we have it in `MinimalForwarder`, `ERC20Permit`, and `ProxyAdmin` so we might want to reconsider those.\r\n\r\n> The version number I believe is wrong, it should be \"last updated v4.9.1\" The commit \"13d5e0466a9855e9305119ed383e54fc913fdc60\" to \"Make Ownable's initial owner explicit (https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/pull/4267)\" comes after the 4.9.0 tag.\r\n\r\nWe have a release cycle (see [RELEASING.md](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/8de6eba8a37d2ece73cb6f0fc7154cdba3619fc0/RELEASING.md)) designed to release from the `release-v4.9` branch so that each time the `patch` is bumped, we only include selected changes cherry picking from `master`.\r\n\r\nI'm explaining this to also outline that the imprecision in the Ownable comments is not yet released and distributed, it's rather a change we should definitely fix before the next 5.0 major, thanks for reporting @nxt3d.\r\n\r\nI'll label it as a good first issue if someone wants to take it, otherwise, we'll eventually revisit it before 5.0 ðŸ˜ƒ ",
